# JavaScript Function Basics

```javascript
// Function declaration
function square(number) {
    return number * number;
}

// Function usage
const result = square(5);
console.log(result); // Outputs: 25
```

### Function Declaration Example

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[Call Function] --> B[Execute Function Body]
    B --> C[Return Value]
    C --> D[Receive Result]
```

# Function Expressions and Arrow Functions

```javascript
// Function expression
const greet = function(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
};

// Arrow function
const add = (a, b) => a + b;

// Usage
console.log(greet('Alice')); // Outputs: Hello, Alice!
console.log(add(2, 3)); // Outputs: 5
```

### Comparison of Function Types

| Type | Syntax | `this` Binding | Suitable For |
|------|--------|----------------|--------------|
| Function Declaration | Standard | Dynamic | Hoisting |
| Function Expression | Standard | Dynamic | More control |
| Arrow Function | Concise | Lexical | Inline callbacks |

# Advanced Function Concepts

```javascript
// Closure
function outerFunction(outerVariable) {
    return function innerFunction(innerVariable) {
        console.log('Outer:', outerVariable);
        console.log('Inner:', innerVariable);
    };
}

const newFunction = outerFunction('outside');
newFunction('inside'); // Outputs: Outer: outside, Inner: inside

// Higher-order function
const numbers = [1, 2, 3];
const doubled = numbers.map(num => num * 2);
console.log(doubled); // Outputs: [2, 4, 6]
```

